		<description><![CDATA[Hi Scottie... Regards from Saltillo, Mexico.. Sorry to hear about your disease. Hope you are feeling fine. I got to tell you something. Since I saw you wearing the left hand glove, now its part of my gear every where I go.... I notice some benefits in my performance using it. 1.- Your hand is warm at all time. 2.- Your strings are free from dust and moisture, so they last longer. 3.- Less noise when you play. 4.- Increases your speed. 5.- Protects your fingers from blisters and cuts. And the best of all.... it´s a great tribute for you my dear Master and friend..    I recommend using it at all time. Thanks.]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Hi Scottie&#8230; Regards from Saltillo, Mexico.. Sorry to hear about your disease. Hope you are feeling fine. I got to tell you something. Since I saw you wearing the left hand glove, now its part of my gear every where I go&#8230;. I notice some benefits in my performance using it. 1.- Your hand is warm at all time. 2.- Your strings are free from dust and moisture, so they last longer. 3.- Less noise when you play. 4.- Increases your speed. 5.- Protects your fingers from blisters and cuts. And the best of all&#8230;. it´s a great tribute for you my dear Master and friend..    I recommend using it at all time. Thanks.</p>
