		<title>By: Our Brilliant Mistake</title>
		<link>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/ask-scott/the-gloves.html#comment-17065</link>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Our Brilliant Mistake]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 27 Apr 2016 12:27:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/?p=14110#comment-17065</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Not listened to the video yet but thanks to Scott and purchasing a pair from him a while back it saved me. My fretting hand would twist up in a ball while playing and wearing the glove stopped it. I did find another kind that had no tips and is thinner that works perfect also. It is a crafters glove if you live in the States you can get at Joanne&#039;s Fabric. I wish I started wearing it 35 years ago. Not only does it help the medical issues it also allows for faster playing especially during those really hot days on stage since your hand doesn&#039;t stick to the neck. 
THANKS SCOTT, without asking you about it my days off playing would be over. ]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Not listened to the video yet but thanks to Scott and purchasing a pair from him a while back it saved me. My fretting hand would twist up in a ball while playing and wearing the glove stopped it. I did find another kind that had no tips and is thinner that works perfect also. It is a crafters glove if you live in the States you can get at Joanne&#8217;s Fabric. I wish I started wearing it 35 years ago. Not only does it help the medical issues it also allows for faster playing especially during those really hot days on stage since your hand doesn&#8217;t stick to the neck.<br />
THANKS SCOTT, without asking you about it my days off playing would be over. </p>
]]></content:encoded>
